TI  - Study on prediction of tensile-shear strength of weld spot based on an improved neural network algorithm
T2  - WELDING IN THE WORLD
LA  - English
KW  - Spot welding
KW  - Ultrasonic testing
KW  - BP neural network
KW  - PSO-SVM
KW  - OPTIMIZATION
AB  - Spot welding is one of the main connection methods of automobile parts. The tensile-shear strength of spot welding joint is the most important factor to evaluate the quality of spot weld. In this paper, a large number of spot welding tests and tensile-shear tests of weld samples are carried out. According to the results of destructive tests, the failure forms of weld samples are divided into base metal tear (a), nugget pull out (b), and interface tear (c). The internal relationship between tensile-shear strength and failure forms of weld samples is established. According to the author's previous research work, the characteristic values of ultrasonic signals in time domain, frequency domain, and wavelet packet of weld samples were obtained. A neural network algorithm based on particle swarm optimization support vector machine (PSO-SVM) was designed according to these characteristics of ultrasonic signal characteristics of weld samples. Finally, the traditional back propagation (BP) neural network algorithm and PSO-SVM neural network algorithm are used to predict the tensile-shear strength of weld samples according to the data in the ultrasonic testing signal test set. The experimental results show that the PSO-SVM neural network combined with 9 ultrasonic signal characteristics has higher prediction accuracy than that of traditional BP neural network.
