AB  - Ultrasonic nondestructive testing is widely used in industry due to its wide detection range and high detection efficiency. However, for multi-layer stacked rubber materials, ultrasound is easily affected by noise interference, it is a challenge work to reduce or separate the noise via signal processing. Therefore, a new ultrasonic echo denoising method based on symplectic geometry mode decomposition is proposed. It can fully decompose the useful components and noise components in the signal, and has a good screening effect on the useful components and noise components. In order to verify the effective-ness and robustness of the method, we conduct experimental research on the model with simulated and measured signals. The analysis results show that our method outperforms other noise reduction methods.(c) 2023 Elsevier Ltd. All rights reserved.
